article.headline: Long Beach State 93, UC Irvine 73
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon led Long Beach State with 24 points as the visiting 49ers overcame an early 21-point deficit to beat UC Irvine 93-73 on Saturday in the regular season finale for both schools. UC Irvine had already lost its chance at the regular season Big West Conference championship when Pacific beat Cal Poly earlier Saturday to clinch the title. UC Irvine (16-12, 10-4) had already secured second place and a bye through the first two rounds of the conference tournament and Long Beach State (16-11, 9-5) had locked up third place and a first-round bye. The 49ers extended their winning streak to five games Sunday and ended the Anteaters' winning streak at three. The Anteaters made eight 3-pointers in the game's first eight minutes for a 31-10 lead. They went 10-for-18 from behind the arc in the first half. Long Beach State tightened its defense and forced several fast breaks to close to 39-38 with 1:39 to play in the first half. The 49ers outscored the Anteaters 15-8 to open the second half, and outscored Irvine 53-27 in the second half. Ross Schrader led UC Irvine with 25 points. Shawn Hawkins added 19 points for Long Beach State.
